<div class="plekify-v8-fw">

<!-- ═══ SECTION 2: THE GAP PLEKIFY FILLS ═══════════════════ -->
<section class="v8-band v8-band--alt">
  <div class="v8-contain">
    <span class="v8-annot">The gap Plekify fills</span>
    <h2 class="v8-sh">Wetu handles itinerary presentation.<br><em>Plekify adds the commerce layer.</em></h2>
    <p class="v8-body v8-prose" style="margin-top:.5rem">Wetu does what it does well: itinerary presentation, white-labelling for trade partners, and a polished visual format that consultants know how to use. What it cannot do is transact, rank in search, recover abandoned bookings, support B2B agent pricing tiers, or convert a browsing guest into a paying one.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="v8-contain--wide">
    <table class="v8-gap">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>When a guest…</th><th>Wetu today</th><th>With Plekify on Shopify</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Clicks "Book Now"</td><td class="v8-gap--dim">Email sent to consultant — no online payment</td><td class="v8-gap--strong">Shopify checkout with deposit or instalment payment</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Views the itinerary</td><td class="v8-gap--dim">wetu.com subdomain — not the operator's domain</td><td class="v8-gap--strong">Operator's own branded domain</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Asks about pricing</td><td class="v8-gap--dim">Static price display only — no booking capability</td><td class="v8-gap--strong">Static display plus live checkout when PMS is connected</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Google crawls the page</td><td class="v8-gap--dim">Nothing — JS iframe, not indexed by search engines</td><td class="v8-gap--strong">Full HTML, structured data, automatic sitemap</td></tr>
        <tr><td>AI agent queries inventory</td><td class="v8-gap--dim">Not discoverable by AI assistants</td><td class="v8-gap--strong">Queryable via Shopify Catalog API and UCP</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Abandons without booking</td><td class="v8-gap--dim">No recovery possible</td><td class="v8-gap--strong">Automated Shopify abandoned checkout recovery</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Browses property detail</td><td class="v8-gap--dim">Description and images</td><td class="v8-gap--strong">Rooms, dining, activities, spa, rates — each browseable</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Wants to book accommodation</td><td class="v8-gap--dim">No booking capability — presentation tool only</td><td class="v8-gap--strong">Live availability, real-time pricing, on-domain checkout</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Requests another language</td><td class="v8-gap--dim">Some itinerary translation; wider site does not translate</td><td class="v8-gap--strong">20+ languages across the entire storefront via Markets</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Wants local currency</td><td class="v8-gap--dim">Static display only — no currency conversion</td><td class="v8-gap--strong">130+ currencies, localised pricing at checkout</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ═══ THE GEOGRAPHY PROBLEM ══════════════════════════════ -->
<section class="v8-band">
  <div class="v8-contain">
    <span class="v8-annot">The geography problem</span>
    <h2 class="v8-sh">76.4% of inbound revenue concentrates<br><em>in two regions.</em></h2>
    <p class="v8-body v8-prose" style="margin-top:.6rem">The Western Cape and Kruger account for more than three-quarters of inbound Southern Africa revenue. Every operator knows the strategic case for selling the Waterberg, the Wild Coast, the Eastern Cape, KwaZulu-Natal — but the commercial infrastructure has not kept up with the ambition. Itineraries for secondary destinations built in Wetu live on wetu.com, where they cannot rank in Google, are not discoverable by AI assistants, and offer no way for a guest to book without leaving the operator's brand.</p>
    <p class="v8-body v8-prose" style="margin-top:.5rem">Plekify puts those itineraries on the operator's own domain — full HTML, structured data, automatic sitemaps — where they are indexed by search engines, queryable by AI agents, and bookable without a domain handoff. Geographic spread is not just a policy ambition. It is a commerce problem, and it requires commerce infrastructure to solve.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ═══ SECTION 3: THREE MODES OF AI WORK ══════════════════ -->
<section id="ai-planning" class="v8-band">
  <div class="v8-contain">
    <span class="v8-annot">Three modes of AI itinerary work</span>
    <h2 class="v8-sh">The AI does not replace the consultant.<br><em>It removes the ceiling.</em></h2>
    <p class="v8-body v8-prose" style="margin-top:.5rem">A consultant's itinerary quality is bounded by memory, experience, and time. The pipeline has no such limits — it searches the full Wetu property database, cross-references Google Maps and each property's own site content, and works against hard constraints set by the brief.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="v8-contain--wide">
    <div class="v8-modes">
      <div class="v8-mode">
        <span class="v8-mode__num">01 — Publish</span>
        <div class="v8-mode__title">Human design<br><em>made bookable</em></div>
        <p class="v8-mode__body">An itinerary designed by a consultant in Wetu is synced to Shopify without modification. The AI adds no new selections — it enriches the presentation, structures the commercial layer, and publishes it as a product on the operator's own domain. No change to how consultants currently work. No new tools. No AI involvement if not wanted.</p>
        <span class="v8-mode__tag">Sync &amp; publish · Commerce layer only</span>
      </div>
      <div class="v8-mode v8-mode--feat">
        <span class="v8-mode__num">02 — Enhance</span>
        <div class="v8-mode__title">Existing Wetu<br><em>itinerary upgraded</em></div>
        <p class="v8-mode__body">An existing itinerary in Wetu is passed to the pipeline. The AI evaluates every property selection against the full database — surfacing better-matched alternatives, filling gaps, improving routing, and freshening narrative — then uploads the improved version back to Wetu. The enhancement pipeline runs every leg against the full current Wetu property database — systematically surfacing better-matched properties in under-travelled regions the original itinerary may not have considered.</p>
        <span class="v8-mode__tag">Enhancement pipeline · On behalf of client</span>
      </div>
      <div class="v8-mode">
        <span class="v8-mode__num">03 — Design</span>
        <div class="v8-mode__title">New itinerary<br><em>from brief</em></div>
        <p class="v8-mode__body">A natural-language brief is the only input. The pipeline handles constraint detection, candidate discovery, route validation, commercial structuring, narrative writing, and direct upload to Wetu — then sync to Shopify as a bookable product.</p>
        <span class="v8-mode__tag">Full pipeline · 14 agents</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ═══ SECTION 4: LIVE ITINERARY EXAMPLES ═════════════════ -->
