<!-- ═══ SECTION 5: INSIDE THE PIPELINE ═════════════════════ -->
<div class="v8-band v8-band--pipeline">
  <div class="v8-contain">
    <div class="v8-pipeline__header">
      <span class="v8-annot">Inside the pipeline</span>
      <p class="v8-pipeline__note" style="margin-top:0;padding-top:0;border-top:none">This is not a prompt sent to a chatbot. It is a governed, gated pipeline — each stage validated before the next begins.</p>
      <h2 class="v8-sh" style="margin-top:1rem">From brief to bookable<br><em>in hours, not weeks.</em></h2>
      <p class="v8-body" style="margin-top:.5rem">The pipeline works against a verified intelligence layer built from the full Wetu property database, cross-referenced with Google Maps data and each property's own website content.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="v8-contain">
    <div class="v8-hl" style="margin-top:1rem;margin-bottom:1.25rem">
      <p class="v8-body"><strong class="v8-hl__label">Plekify does not disintermediate the operator.</strong> In every commercial model — including when products are listed on plekify.com — the operator is the merchant of record and the guest data belongs to them, not to Plekify. The consultant stays central to every booking. What Plekify does is close the gap between the moment a client says yes and the moment the payment arrives — giving the operator a way to convert agreement into a completed transaction without sending the guest to another platform.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="v8-contain--wide">
    <div class="v8-pipeline__grid">
      <div class="v8-pipeline__left">
        <ul class="v8-ai-list">
          <li>Hard guest requirements — always/never rules — enforced across every leg</li>
          <li>Anchor events lock first: match days, tee times, flights become immovable before routing begins</li>
          <li>Candidate search combines semantic intent, exact-term matching, and concept-based retrieval</li>
          <li>Route feasibility, transfer timing, and border logic validated computationally before assembly</li>
          <li>Every recommendation carries source provenance — traceable to verified data</li>
          <li>The pipeline stops and asks when it encounters genuine ambiguity. It does not guess.</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="v8-agents">
          <span class="v8-pill">Brief compiler</span>
          <span class="v8-pill">Event locker</span>
          <span class="v8-pill">Candidate ranker</span>
          <span class="v8-pill">Route feasibility</span>
          <span class="v8-pill">Pin selector</span>
          <span class="v8-pill">Itinerary architect</span>
          <span class="v8-pill">Commercial pricing</span>
          <span class="v8-pill">Compliance core</span>
          <span class="v8-pill">Contract builder</span>
          <span class="v8-pill">Narrative writer</span>
          <span class="v8-pill">QA audit gate</span>
          <span class="v8-pill">Wetu uploader</span>
          <span class="v8-pill">Shopify packager</span>
        </div>
        <p class="v8-body v8-sm" style="margin-top:.6rem">14 purpose-built agents. Each has defined inputs, outputs, validation checks, and failure modes.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="v8-pipeline__right">
        <div class="v8-params">
          <div class="v8-params__title">Planning parameters — example brief</div>
          <div class="v8-params__row"><span class="v8-params__key">Travel style</span><span class="v8-params__val">Luxury · Ultra-luxury · Adventure</span></div>
          <div class="v8-params__row"><span class="v8-params__key">Pace</span><span class="v8-params__val">Relaxed — 3 to 4 nights per stop</span></div>
          <div class="v8-params__row"><span class="v8-params__key">Anchor event</span><span class="v8-params__val v8-params__val--anchor">FIFA WC Quarter Final<br>Mexico City · 4 Jul</span></div>
          <div class="v8-params__row"><span class="v8-params__key">Always include</span><span class="v8-params__val">Private game reserve<br>One Relais &amp; Châteaux property</span></div>
          <div class="v8-params__row"><span class="v8-params__key">Never include</span><span class="v8-params__val v8-params__val--never">Shared tented camps<br>Dormitory accommodation</span></div>
          <div class="v8-params__row"><span class="v8-params__key">Budget</span><span class="v8-params__val">$800 – $1 200 per person / night</span></div>
        </div>
        <p class="v8-body v8-sm" style="margin-top:.65rem">These parameters become hard constraints applied across every candidate, every leg, and every recommendation.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="v8-contain">
    <div class="v8-hl" style="margin-top:1.5rem">
      <p class="v8-body"><strong class="v8-hl__label">On enhancement:</strong> Most Wetu itineraries were built at a point in time against the properties a consultant happened to know. The Wetu database has grown substantially since. The enhancement pipeline runs every leg against the full current database — a systematic upgrade done programmatically and uploaded back into the client's Wetu account.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

